main event: Multiple unidentified flying object sightings reported in Houston, Texas on various dates in January 1966.
interesting points: Numerous reports documented different sightings including a bright white light, a red and pink light, and V-shaped objects with red lights., The sightings occurred under various conditions, including day and night., Significant emphasis was placed on the lack of photographic evidence in each report., Observations lasted from 1 to 30 minutes, depending on the incident., Despite numerous reports, the conclusions often stated insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: various unidentified flying objects including bright lights and V-shaped objects
witness description: civilians including a fireworks store manager and others
